# ===========================
# Database Configuration
# ===========================

# Development database (local testing, can be cleared)
# Safe to reset with: npm run db:reset
# Used for: npm run dev, PM2 staging-backend
DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db?journal_mode=WAL"

# Production database (deployed, persistent data)
# NEVER cleared - data is preserved across deployments
# Used for: PM2 main process (port 8080)
# Uncomment for production deployment:
# DATABASE_URL="file:./prod.db?journal_mode=WAL"

# ===========================
# Notes
# ===========================
# - WAL mode (Write-Ahead Logging) enables better concurrency
# - dev.db: Safe to clear, used for development and testing
# - prod.db: Persistent data, only modified via migrations
# - PM2 processes set DATABASE_URL via ecosystem.config.js
# - See knowledge-base/sqlite/database-tools.md for details
